watson.config.comment.actionreverse: If enabled, it won't show the reverse action of a player that happend
watson.config.comment.amountrowes:
Sets amount of rows used for autopage feature
CoreProtect Only
watson.config.comment.autopage: If enabled, this allows to automatically step thru max allowed pages
watson.config.comment.chattimeoutseconds: The minimum amount of seconds between sent chat messages by the mod
watson.config.comment.coreprotectcommand: Choose the command you can use for CoreProtect
watson.config.comment.disablecpmessages:
Disables CoreProtect lookup messages
This will disable the spam from auto pages.
watson.config.comment.displayed: If true, watson will draw stuff
watson.config.comment.groupingoresincrea: Ores are grouped even in creative
watson.config.comment.highlight:
What gets highlighted in chat
All entries should have this order: <style><color>;<text>
watson.config.comment.highlightcasesensi: If enabled, the highlight patterns will be case sensitive
watson.config.comment.highlightsound:
Set the highlight sound with a sound event key
As example entity.cat.hiss and block.anvil.break
More sound events to be found at:
https://www.digminecraft.com/lists/sound_list_pc.php
watson.config.comment.highlightsoundenab: Enables making sound when something gets highlight.
watson.config.comment.highlightsoundvolu: Sets the volume that the highlight sound will play.
watson.config.comment.linkedcreation: If true, block creations will be linked by vectors
watson.config.comment.linkeddestruction: If true, block destruction will be linked by vectors
watson.config.comment.disablelbmessages:
Disables LogBlock lookup messages
This will disable the spam.
watson.config.comment.maxautopages: Amount of pages that is allowed when auto page is enabled
watson.config.comment.maxautopagesloop: Amount of automatic stepped thru pages
watson.config.comment.onlyoreblock: Only shows block in block space
watson.config.comment.orelinewidth: Uses this linewidth for all ores if oreOutlineThicker is enabled
watson.config.comment.oreoutlinethicker:
Ore outline thicker when enabled
If false, uses the integer for outline in watson blocks list config
Default line width: 1
watson.config.comment.outlineshown: If true, wireframe outline will be displayed
watson.config.comment.overridingactions:
What actions gets overriden
All entries should have this order: <playername><action>;<reverse action>
watson.config.comment.pagelines: Number of chat lines in a page
watson.config.comment.plugin: Which plugin does the server use
watson.config.comment.postcount: Number of edits to be run post
watson.config.comment.precount: Number of edits to be fetched
watson.config.comment.disableprmessages:
Disables Prism lookup messages
This will disable the spam.
watson.config.comment.reformatqueryresul: Format query in chat more compact if enabled
watson.config.comment.regioninfotimeouts: Sets the timeout in seconds when right clicking with a wooden sword
watson.config.comment.selectionshown: If enabled selection will be shown
watson.config.comment.smallerrenderbox: Blocks will have a smaller rendering box
watson.config.comment.ssplayerdirectory: Subdirectory named after the currently selected player is created to hold screenshots of his edits if enabled
watson.config.comment.ssplayersuffix: Name of current selected player is appended to screenshot files
watson.config.comment.teleportcommand:
Sets teleport command
The different format to use inside the placeholders are:
i for integer or d for decimal numbers
Placeholders to use are:
{x:format}, {y:format}, {z:format}, {world}
watson.config.comment.timeordereddeposit:
If true, ore deposits should be numeric labeled when mined
When false it gets ordered in descending order of rareness of the ore
watson.config.comment.usechathighlights: If true, chat highlighter will be enabled
watson.config.comment.disablejoinmessage: If true, it will disable the join messages that are sent by Watson
watson.config.comment.watsonprefix: The start of all Watson commands, without a slash
watson.hotkey.comment.coreinspect:
Executes /co i
(Set Plugin in Generic to CoreProtect and only works with CoreProtect)
watson.hotkey.comment.queryafter:
Query edits after
(Set Plugin in Generic to LogBlock and only works with LogBlock)
watson.hotkey.comment.querybefore:
Query edits before
(Set Plugin in Generic to LogBlock and only works with LogBlock)
watson.error.anno.position: Use the LogBlock tool to set a position

watson.gui.label.ledger.info.source:
Sources are comma seperated.
To invert a source put '!' before the source.
Examples for a source are 'Annevdl29' and '@tnt'.
watson.gui.label.ledger.info.time:
You can specify durations with 's' seconds, 'm' minute, 'h' hour, 'd' day and 'w' week.
For example '7w4d31m42s'.
